PN,31901
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FHere are some lessons from recent
OL,7,Fhistory.
OL,9,FHow it can all go horribly wrong. How
OL,10,Fluck and fine margins mark the
OL,11,Fboundary between triumph and disaster.
OL,12,FHow so often you don't see that
OL,13,Fboundary until you've stepped over it.
OL,15,FThe setting is Libya. It's 2011.
OL,16,FWestern warplanes are trying to bomb
OL,17,Fout of business an autocratic regime
OL,18,Fthat's just turned its guns on
OL,19,Fthousands of its own citizens. Sound
OL,20,Ffamiliar?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FSpecifically, it's the early hours of
OL,7,FAugust 22. I'm in a cramped little car
OL,8,Fthat stinks of the fumes from several
OL,9,Fjerry cans of petrol, part of the
OL,10,Funwieldy kit of cameras, body armour,
OL,11,Fand generators needed to carry the ITV
OL,12,FNews team through this chaos.
OL,14,FITV News Correspondent John Ray was
OL,15,Fsent to Libya in 2011 to capture the
OL,16,Fdramatic fall of Muammar Gaddafi in
OL,17,Fthe Arab Spring
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FI am a very nervous correspondent,
OL,7,Fwondering whether I will hear the
OL,8,Fburst of machine gun fire I expect any
OL,9,Fmoment to finish us. Or whether I'll
OL,10,Fbe dead before the sound of the
OL,11,Fbullets reaches me.
OL,13,FBut my team is top rate: cameraman Rob
OL,14,FBowles, editor Patrick O'Ryan-Roeder,
OL,15,Four security man Garry Curtis and two
OL,16,Fvery brave local drivers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FWe believe we're heading to a safe
OL,7,Fhaven for the night. But, we're about
OL,8,Fto hand ourselves over to the regime
OL,9,Fof Colonel Muammar Gaddafi, to check
OL,10,Finto a gilded prison.
OL,12,FWe've been told the Rixos Hotel, home
OL,13,Fthroughout the crisis to the world's
OL,14,Fmedia, has been liberated. We've been
OL,15,Fpromised this by two separate sources.
OL,16,FUnfortunately, their source is the
OL,17,Fsame man ... and he is wrong.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FAt the hotel's grand entrance, we're
OL,7,Fgreeted by two impressive sights. The
OL,8,Fportrait, intact, of a haughty Gaddafi
OL,9,Fadorning a reception.
OL,11,FAnd then, a group of journalists,
OL,12,Fmoving like dazed extras in the final
OL,13,Freel of a disaster movie, who mistake
OL,14,Fus for a force come to free them.
OL,16,F"Can you get me a ticket to Paris?"
OL,17,Fone asks me.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FWithin moments, a group of gun-toting
OL,7,Fregime fighters turns up. There will
OL,8,Fbe no tickets to Paris, or to
OL,9,Fanywhere, for the hotel's inmates.
OL,11,FThis was the dispiriting climax to
OL,12,Fseveral days of great excitement and
OL,13,Fgreat fear as we witnessed and, as
OL,14,Fthis ITV News series says, reported
OL,15,Fhistory.
OL,17,FWe'd followed the rebels' advance into
OL,18,Fthe capital. I'd seen fighters shot in
OL,19,Ffront of me. We were trapped for a
OL,20,Fwhile at the front line and came under
OL,21,Fmortar fire.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FI learned, as we fled the scene lying
OL,7,Fflat on the back of a speeding truck,
OL,8,Fthe difference between the sound of
OL,9,Foutgoing gunfire and the whizz of
OL,10,Fbullets flying just above our heads.
OL,12,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,13,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,14,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,15,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,17,FThen, disaster. As we drove down a
OL,18,Ftree-lined road parallel to the
OL,19,Fbattle, I remember seeing ahead that
OL,20,Fone, a blackened stump, was still
OL,21,Fburning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FAt the precise moment we passed, it
OL,7,Ftoppled, smashing the windscreen of
OL,8,Four pick-up and then bouncing over the
OL,9,Froof.
OL,11,FOn the back of the truck, as ever and
OL,12,Fby choice, as if leading us into
OL,13,Fbattle, had stood our fixer. A
OL,14,FMancunian Libyan named Essam. An
OL,15,Fenthusiast for the uprising, our only
OL,16,FArabic speaker, and an integral part
OL,17,Fof the team.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31909
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FNow he lay motionless. For a
OL,7,Fhorrifying moment, we were convinced
OL,8,Fhe was dead. But Garry, a trained
OL,9,Fmedic, found breath in his body. His
OL,10,Fhelmet had saved his life.
OL,12,FStill, the injuries were significant.
OL,13,FWe spent the rest of the morning
OL,14,Ffinding a field hospital. ITN arranged
OL,15,Fsafe passage back to the UK.
OL,17,FBut by now the story had raced ahead
OL,18,Fof us. The rebels had reached the
OL,19,Fcapital. That night, we felt under
OL,20,Fhuge pressure to follow them into
OL,21,FTripoli.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31910
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FSo after much discussion and against
OL,7,Fthe initial judgment of more
OL,8,Fexperienced members of the team ` and
OL,9,Fwith two new cars and two young
OL,10,Fdrivers from the village that had been
OL,11,Fat our base - we set off into the
OL,12,Fdarkness.
OL,14,FWe reached Green Square as the victory
OL,15,Fparty ended. When I look back on the
OL,16,Freport we filed, I can see I share
OL,17,Fsome of the joy and optimism of the
OL,18,Fmoment. I think ` or at least hope -
OL,19,Fit's all over.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31911
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FBut it wasn't. We were warned that
OL,7,Fregime soldiers were coming. We needed
OL,8,Fto find somewhere to spend the night.
OL,10,FI woke the next morning in the Rixos
OL,11,Fto the oppressive reality of the
OL,12,Fcatastrophic blunder I'd made to put
OL,13,Fthe team into the hands of the regime.
OL,15,FUp to that point, even at the front
OL,16,Fline, if in doubt, we could get out.
OL,17,FIn the hotel, we felt trapped like
OL,18,Frats.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31912
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FThere followed two or three surreal
OL,7,Fdays. The battle for Tripoli raged
OL,8,Faround us. A round came through our
OL,9,Fwindow. We worked, we reported, we
OL,10,Ffiled stories. It helped keep our
OL,11,Fminds off recurring and uncomfortable
OL,12,Fquestions.
OL,14,FWhat happens when the rebels come? Is
OL,15,Fthis where the regime will make its
OL,16,Flast stand? What will they do to the
OL,17,Fhostages? Release us, or kill us?
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31913
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FEscape seemed the best option. Our
OL,7,Ffirst attempt didn't go well. We
OL,8,Floaded up our cars with a simple plan
OL,9,Fto style it out down the hotel's wide
OL,10,Fdriveway.
OL,12,FBut we were stopped and then held at
OL,13,Fgunpoint by a very twitchy group of
OL,14,Fyoung regime loyalists. They were
OL,15,Farmed with AK47s.
OL,17,FThey shouted and pointed their guns at
OL,18,Fus. A lot. Then they took our
OL,19,Fpassports. Worse, they accused us of
OL,20,Fbeing Israeli spies.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31914
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FThese were anxious hours, in which our
OL,7,Ffate seemed to depend on the whims of
OL,8,Fa gang of jumpy teenagers. And yet,
OL,9,Fafter a while, inexplicably, they
OL,10,Fseemed to lose interest in us. I don't
OL,11,Fknow why.
OL,13,FEventually, we headed back to our
OL,14,Frooms. There, I retrieved from my bag
OL,15,Fa tube of toothpaste that had Hebrew
OL,16,Fwriting on the side. I put it above in
OL,17,Fthe ceiling tiles. It might still be
OL,18,Fthere.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G14/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31915
SC,0015
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FFor the next attempt to bust out ` a
OL,7,Fplan hatched by Rob and Patrick - we
OL,8,Fabandoned the cars and headed for a
OL,9,Ffire door at the rear of the hotel. We
OL,10,Fran as fast as middle-aged men in flak
OL,11,Fjackets can across tennis courts and
OL,12,Fthen shimmied over a low wall.
OL,14,FA van was passing. We flagged it down.
OL,15,FThe driver took us in ` and then to
OL,16,Four horror, headed straight to the
OL,17,Fsound of fierce battle close by.
OL,19,FHe stopped only when he came to a
OL,20,Fbullet-ridden car slewed across the
OL,21,Flane ahead. A corpse lay next to it.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G15/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31916
SC,0016
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FThe moment of liberation was sweet but
OL,7,Fundramatic. A U-turn, a short drive,
OL,8,Fat pace, down the wrong side of the
OL,9,Fhighway, and then a turn into an area
OL,10,Fheld by rebels. A call to the newsdesk
OL,11,Fin London that we were out and safe.
OL,13,FThere was one last act to return to
OL,14,Fthe hotel for our two drivers. More
OL,15,Fthan anyone, their lives had been in
OL,16,Fperil.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G16/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31917
SC,0017
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FIf they'd been caught by our guards,
OL,7,Fas two young men from an opposition
OL,8,Ftown helping "foreign spies" ... we
OL,9,Fcould all work out the likely
OL,10,Fconsequences.
OL,12,FPatrick and Garry went back to the
OL,13,FRixos and arrived just as the real Red
OL,14,FCrescent turned up.
OL,16,FWhat happened to our captors, I never
OL,17,Ffound out. The siege of the Rixos
OL,18,Fended peacefully, and a couple of days
OL,19,Flater, I was heading out of Libya with
OL,20,Fa story to tell my wife.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G17/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31918
SC,0018
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FIt is not a story of journalistic
OL,7,Ftriumph but is one of survival; of
OL,8,Fdisaster, just about averted.
OL,10,FPerhaps it's the same for Libya.
OL,11,FGaddafi was tracked down and
OL,12,Fbutchered. But the uprising did not
OL,13,Fresult in the kind of future that the
OL,14,FWest had promised.
OL,16,FToday, it is divided between two rival
OL,17,Fgovernments and is best known as a key
OL,18,Fjumping-off point for migrants headed
OL,19,Fto Europe.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G18/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,350,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31919
SC,0019
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774144984
OL,3,CWhat being held hostage in Libya
OL,4,Ctaught me about war
OL,6,FAll this is fresh in my mind as I
OL,7,Fwatch Iran and wonder about the laws
OL,8,Fof unintended consequences and whether
OL,9,Fthe world has already stepped over one
OL,10,Fof those invisible borders between
OL,11,Ftriumph and disaster.
OL,13,FReporting History sees journalists
OL,14,Fjoin News At Ten anchor Tom Bradby to
OL,15,Frevisit their remarkable on-the-day
OL,16,Freports of the defining events of the
OL,17,Fmodern age. Listen to the episodes
OL,18,Fbelow...
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G19/19
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
